{"title_page": "Gheorghe Laz\u0103r National College (Bucharest)", "text_new": "{{Infobox school\n| name=Gheorghe Laz\u0103r National College\n| native_name=\n| image= Bucuresti, Romania, Liceul Gheorghe Lazar; B-II-m-B-18689.JPG\n| image_size = \n| streetaddress = Regina Elisabeta Boulevard no. 48\n| city=Bucharest\n| country=Romania\n| coordinates = \n| fundingtype = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]]\n| established=\t1860\n| status = Open\n| category = Middle School and High School\n| grades = [[Fifth grade|5]] to [[Twelfth grade|12]]\n| gender = [[Mixed-sex education|coeducation]]\n| age_range = 11-19\n| enrolment = ~1,000\n| average_class_size = 28\n| medium_of_language = Romanian\n| hours_in_day = 5-7\n| campus_type = [[Urban area|Urban]]\n| nickname=\n| founder =\n| website       = {{url|cnlazar.ro}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Gheorghe Laz\u0103r National College''' ({{lang-ro|Colegiul Na\u021bional Gheorghe Laz\u0103r}}) is a high school located in central [[Bucharest]], [[Romania]], at the southeast corner of the [[Ci\u0219migiu Gardens]], on the corner of Bulevardul Regina Elisabeta. One of the most prestigious secondary education institutions in Romania, it was named after the [[Transylvania]]n educator [[Gheorghe Laz\u0103r]], who taught at the [[Saint Sava College]].  Founded in 1860, it is the second oldest high school in Bucharest.\n\n== History ==\nOn January 18, 1860, [[Alexandru Ioan Cuza]] founded the second gymnasium with teaching in Romanian in Bucharest and gave it the name of [[Gheorghe Laz\u0103r]], who \"was the refounder of the nation's schools\". The high school's [[anniversary]] has been celebrated from then on this date, when the school first opened its doors.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.schoolandcollegelistings.com/RO/Bucharest/106447749391169/Gheorghe-Lazar-High-School|title=Gheorghe Lazar High School, Bulevardul Regina Elisabeta Nr. 48, Sector 5, Bucharest (2020)|website=www.schoolandcollegelistings.com|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nThe decree of the establishment of the high school bears the signature of [[Charles I of Romania|King Carol I]] and the date 20 May 1890.\u00a0In the autumn of [[1890]], the new place near [[Ci\u0219migiu Gardens|Ci\u015fmigiu]] was inaugurated. The construction, designed by architect F. G. Muntureanu, who studied in England, is an architectural jewel of elegant sobriety, combining several styles: from the [[Br\u00e2ncovenesc style|br\u00e2ncovenesc]] to the [[Neoclassical architecture|neoclassical]] English one. It is not by chance that Laz\u0103r has been compared to the [[Paris]]ian high schools near the [[Jardin du Luxembourg|Luxembourg Garden]].\n\nIn [[1931]], the new wing of the high school was built at the initiative of the general assembly of parents, which allowed the development of new laboratories, the elegant amphitheatre, the semi-basement buffet. In the [[Stalinist era|Stalinist Era]], the high school suffered. First, it was given a number instead of its old name: it became Middle School No. 22. It shared the building with a new girls' school and in [[1949]] the high school was transferred, along with the archive and everything else (paintings by former directors, books, documents, commemorative plaques), at the former high school \"Spiru Haret\". Mechanic Gheorghe Dinu  saved from destruction the Book of Honor of the high school, hiding it in the attic of the school. In [[1955]] the ministry decided to return to the old name, the resumption of possession of the place and the establishment of mixed schools.\n\nSome remarkable achievements of the 1990-1997 period are the radical strengthening the school's building under the administration of principal Nicolae Novac, the high school's affiliation to [[UNESCO]] (1992), twinning with the French high school \"Jean Monnet\" in [[Jou\u00e9-l\u00e8s-Tours|Jou\u00e9-les-Tours]], protocol initiated and consolidated by Prof. Roxana Veleanovici (1991), receiving the National College title (1995).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://teenpress.ro/liceul-meu/colegiul-national-gheorghe-lazar/|title=Colegiul National \"Gheorghe Lazar\" {{!}} Teen Press|language=ro-RO|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cnlazar.ro/index.php/cuvantul-directorilor/istoric/|title=Istoric C.N. Lazar {{!}} COLEGIU NATIONAL GHEORGHE LAZAR|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n== Motto and Symbols ==\nFrom the mid-2010s the high school's motto has been \"''Pentru unii un liceu, pentru noi un mod de via\u021b\u0103''\", meaning \"''For some a high school, for us a way of life''\". Previously it was \"''Acest liceu este f\u0103cut pentru \u00eenving\u0103torii vie\u0163ii\"''',''''' meaning ''\"This high school is made for life's victors\".''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://teenpress.ro/liceul-meu/colegiul-national-gheorghe-lazar/|title=Colegiul National \"Gheorghe Lazar\" {{!}} Teen Press|language=ro-RO|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jurnalul.antena3.ro/special-jurnalul/reportaje/liceul-gheorghe-lazar-bucuresti-pentru-unii-un-liceu-pentru-noi-un-mod-de-viata-686643.html|title=Liceul \"Gheorghe Laz\u0103r\" Bucure\u0219ti: \"Pentru unii un liceu, pentru noi, un mod de via\u021b\u0103!\"|website=jurnalul.antena3.ro|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://prezi.com/kuft1geenvum/lazarul-pentru-unii-un-liceu-pentru-noi-un-mod-de-viata/|title=Laz\u0103rul, pentru unii un liceu, pentru noi un mod de via\u021b\u0103|website=prezi.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nThe motto of the [[student council]] is \"''Chaque enfant qu'on enseigne est un homme qu'on gagne''\", in English \"''Every child we teach is a person we win''\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.consiliulelevilorlazar.ro/|title=Consiliul Elevilor Colegiului National \"Gheorghe Lazar\"|website=www.consiliulelevilorlazar.ro|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cnlazar.ro/index.php/elevi/consiliul-elevilor/|title=Consiliul elevilor {{!}} COLEGIU NATIONAL GHEORGHE LAZAR|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nThe old [[anthem]] of the high school, on a text by V. I. P\u0103un and a song by G. Br\u0103tianu, was presented for the first time during the first celebration of the patron's commemoration on 18 January 1892. In [[1910]], on the occasion of the school's semicentennial, the high school orchestra and choir performed under the baton of Master Ion Costescu a new variant of the anthem, on the conductor's music.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cnlazar.ro/index.php/cuvantul-directorilor/imnul-gh-lazar-2006/|title=Imnul C.N. Lazar {{!}} COLEGIU NATIONAL GHEORGHE LAZAR|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n==Notable alumni==\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n*[[Ion Andreescu]]\n*[[Alexandru Athanasiu]]\n*[[Grigore B\u0103jenaru]]\n*[[Ion Barbu]]\n*[[Emilian Bratu]]\n*[[George C\u0103linescu]]\n*[[Elie Carafoli]]\n*[[George Ciprian]]\n*[[Liviu Ciulei]]\n*[[Miti\u021b\u0103 Constantinescu]]\n*[[Eugen Filotti]]\n*[[Alexandru Ghika]]\n*[[Marcel Janco]]\n*[[Leon Lichtblau]]\n*[[Gabriel Liiceanu]]\n*[[Dinu Lipatti]]\n*[[Marius Nasta]]\n*[[Camil Petrescu]]\n*[[Florian Pitti\u0219]]\n*[[Alexandru Proca]]\n*[[Ilie \u0218teflea]]\n*[[Valeriu Stoica]]\n*[[Constantin T\u0103nase]]\n*[[Urmuz]]\n*[[Tudor Vianu]]\n*[[Vasile Voiculescu]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060520152204/http://www.cnlazar.ro/en/index.php Website]\n*[http://revistalzr.ro The student newspaper - Revista LZR]\n*[http://www.trupaas.ro The theatre group - Trupa de teatru AS]{{coord|44|26|6.06|N|26|5|24.73|E|display=title}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gheorghe Lazar National College (Bucharest)}}\n[[Category:High schools in Bucharest]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1860]]\n[[Category:Historic monuments in Bucharest]]\n[[Category:1860 establishments in Romania]]\n[[Category:National Colleges in Romania]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox school\n| name=Gheorghe Laz\u0103r Natio